    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <date>Wednesday 16th</date>
                <add>?</add>
                <date>Shevat(Feb), 1865</date>
            </p>
            <p>My friend and the friend of the Almighty:</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I have received the manuscript but the <date>February</date>
                issue<lb/> only yesterday. In <date>January</date>, you did not send me the usual
                ten copies.<lb/> Of the <date>February</date> number, however, you must be good
                enough to send me at<lb/> once 12-15 copies, so that I might send several to
                    <placeName>Germany</placeName> on <date>Friday</date>.<lb/> Have you no
                opportunity to send it along with someone as you used to?<lb/> For I should be glad
                to come and get them if you will send me the address<lb/> in <placeName>New
                    York</placeName>. Otherwise, send them to my home by express, <placeName>112
                    West 25th <sic>ST.</sic>,<lb/> near 7th Avenue</placeName>, but please write the
                address clearly. Unfortunately my<lb/> speculation with my
                    “<persName>Esther</persName>” did not succeed. You, too, did not want to<lb/>
                support me properly. I shall therefore send you, tomorrow, the trans-<lb/>lation for
                publication in the “Occident”, where it will therefore appear<add>?</add><lb/> But
                should like to ask that you stereotype it, but, in any case, to<lb/> make of it a
                separate audition. You therefore need not make the “Occident”<lb/> any larger.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I have so much to speak to you about, but you are so often<lb/>
                unapproachable. I heard that you were here last <date>Sunday</date> at a meeting
                of<lb/> the Delegates. I ran with my old feet to <persName>Sternberger</persName>
                and no one knew<lb/> about you.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Here there is again a great <add>?</add>. In the <placeName>Henry
                    Street</placeName><lb/> synagogue they want to imitate the <placeName>Green
                    Street</placeName> Synagogue and put the<lb/> gentle dates on the gravestones. I
                am opposed and I have my reasons<lb/> and my views. I shall also come in conflict
                with <persName>Wise</persName> on account of<lb/> the burning of his heretical
                works. But I stand here like a lonely<lb/> shrub in the wilderness. What do people
                say about my warning? The<lb/> passage against <persName>Wise</persName> and
                    <persName>Einhorn</persName>, you have translated exactly. I await<lb/> your
                answer by return post.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Sincerely yours,</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <persName role="author">Jonah of the house of Bondi</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
